{
  "local_port": 39184,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I take admission in JNU?",
  "response": "Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU) is one of India's premier universities, known for its emphasis on social sciences, humanities, and scientific research. To take admission in JNU, you need to follow these steps:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Choose Your Course**\nJNU offers programs at the undergraduate (UG), postgraduate (PG), M.Phil., and Ph.D. levels. Decide which course you want to pursue. Popular courses include:\n- **UG**: BA (Hons) in languages, social sciences, and international studies.\n- **PG**: MA, MSc, M.Tech, MBA.\n- **Research Programs**: M.Phil. and Ph.D.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Check Eligibility Criteria**\nEach course has its own eligibility criteria. For example:\n- **UG**: 10+2 with a minimum percentage (varies by course).\n- **PG**: Bachelor\u2019s degree in a relevant field with a minimum percentage (usually 50% or above).\n- **Ph.D.**: Master\u2019s degree with a qualifying cut-off in the entrance exam.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Appear for the Entrance Exam**\nJNU conducts **JNU Entrance Exam (JNUEE)** for most of its courses. The exam is usually held in **May/June** every year. Key details:\n- The exam is conducted by the **National Testing Agency (NTA)**.\n- It is computer-based (CBT) and includes multiple-choice questions (MCQs).\n- The syllabus and pattern vary for different courses.\n\nExemptions:\n- For some courses, candidates with **UGC-NET/JRF** or **CSIR-NET/JRF** qualifications may be exempted from the entrance exam.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Fill the Application Form**\n- Visit the official JNU admissions portal: [https://admissions.jnu.ac.in](https://admissions.jnu.ac.in).\n- Register and fill out the application form.\n- Upload required documents such as your photograph, signature, and academic certificates.\n- Pay the application fee online.\n- Submit the form before the deadline.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Check the Merit List**\nAfter the entrance exam, JNU releases a **merit list** based on your performance. The merit list is course-specific and includes the names of shortlisted candidates.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Attend the Interview (if applicable)**\nFor some courses (e.g., M.Phil./Ph.D.), shortlisted candidates may need to attend an interview or viva voce.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Complete the Admission Process**\nIf you are selected:\n- Pay the admission fee.\n- Submit required documents for verification.\n- Attend the orientation program and start your classes.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Tips**\n- Keep an eye on the official JNU website and NTA notifications.\n- Prepare well for the entrance exam, focusing on your chosen subject.\n- If you belong to a reserved category (SC/ST/OBC/EWS/PwD), ensure you have the necessary certificates.\n\nFor more details, visit the official JNU admissions website or contact the university's admission office. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
